"title": "5735: sexuality",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5735: sexuality",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Men and women are intended to complement one another and to take pleasure in one another. God has provided for the full and glad expression of this in marriage.</p>\n<h2>Sexuality comes from God</h2>\n<h3>It was created by God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:27\">GEN 1:27</a></strong></p>\n<h3>God intended men and women to complement one another</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:11\">1CO 11:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:18-Gen2:22\">GEN 2:18–2:22</a></p>\n<h2>Sexual differences</h2>\n<h3>In strength</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:7\">1PE 3:7</a></p>\n<h3>In role</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:3-1Cor11:5\">1CO 11:3–11:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:34-1Cor14:35\">1CO 14:34–14:35</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:22-Eph5:25\">EPH 5:22–5:25</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:18-Col3:19\">COL 3:18–3:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim2:12-1Tim2:14\">1TI 2:12–2:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:1\">1PE 3:1</a></p>\n<h3>In dress</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut22:5\">DEU 22:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:14-1Cor11:15\">1CO 11:14–11:15</a></p>\n<h2>Sexual activity</h2>\n<h3>It was ordained by God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:28\">GEN 1:28</a></strong> <em>This command was made before the fall, and no guilt attaches to it.</em></p>\n<h3>Marriage in its proper context</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:23-Gen2:24\">GEN 2:23–2:24</a></strong> <em>“one flesh” implies both bodily union and an inseparable intimate relationship.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:4-Matt19:6\">MAT 19:4–19:6</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:6-Mark10:9\">MRK 10:6–10:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:2-1Cor7:4\">1CO 7:2–7:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:31-Eph5:33\">EPH 5:31–5:33</a></p>\n<h3>Sexual desire</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song4:3-Song4:15\">SNG 4:3–4:15</a></strong> <em>“Song of Songs” celebrates the beauty of sex in a loving context. It contains much delicate and intimate imagery that applies directly to human lovers and can also be applied to Jesus Christ and the church.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:16\">GEN 3:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song1:2-Song1:4\">SNG 1:2–1:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song4:16\">SNG 4:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song7:11-Song7:13\">SNG 7:11–7:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song8:10\">SNG 8:10</a></p>\n<h3>Abstinence is possible</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:12\">MAT 19:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:1\">1CO 7:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:5\">1CO 7:5</a></p>\n<h2>Perversions of sexuality</h2>\n<h3>Adultery</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:14\">EXO 20:14</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:18\">DEU 5:18</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:4\">HEB 13:4</a></p>\n<h3>Lust</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:28\">MAT 5:28</a></strong> <em>Lust may also lead to other sexual sins.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:19\">EPH 4:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:3\">EPH 5:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:5\">COL 3:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet4:3\">1PE 4:3</a></p>\n<h3>Promiscuity</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut22:13-Deut22:21\">DEU 22:13–22:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:24\">ROM 1:24</a></p>\n<h3>Prostitution</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:29\">LEV 19:29</a></p>\n<h3>Homosexuality</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:26-Rom1:27\">ROM 1:26–1:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen19:4-Gen19:7\">GEN 19:4–19:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev18:22\">LEV 18:22</a></p>\n<h3>Bestiality</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod22:19\">EXO 22:19</a></p>\n<h3>Sexual perversion will be punished</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:9-1Cor6:10\">1CO 6:9–6:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:8\">REV 21:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:15\">REV 22:15</a></p>\n<h3>Sexual perversion can be cleansed</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:11\">1CO 6:11</a></p>\n<h2>Sexuality is transcended in heaven</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:30\">MAT 22:30</a></strong></p>",
